      "published_date": "2026-02-23T21:11:15.000Z",
      "text": "# New York PSC Reforms Grid Connection for Large Electricity Users\n\nPublished: 2026-02-23T21:11:15+00:00\n\n## Summary\n\nThe New York State Public Service Commission (PSC) has initiated a new proceeding (Case 26-E-0045) to reform and define interconnection policies for large electricity users. The move aims to support both modernization and economic development goals. This follows Governor's direction to attract new businesses and protect ratepayers. The PSC's goal is to ensure data centers and other energy-intensive operations, such as advanced manufacturing facilities, are responsible for the costs they impose on the electric system. The proceeding will also consider opportunities for beneficial reuse of waste heat through coordination with utility thermal energy networks. The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission is also considering a generic rulemaking on large load interconnections in response to a Department of Energy directive.\n\n## Story\n\nNew York PSC Reforms Grid Connection for Lar",
