      "text": "# New Data Center Announced; SWEPCO Role Cited in Supporting Local Economic Growth\n\nPublished: 2026-02-23T15:45:00-05:00\nAuthor: Southwestern Electric Power Company\nType: Press Release\n\n## Summary\n\nSouthwestern Electric Power Co. (SWEPCO) has announced a new data center investment from Amazon, described as the most significant economic development win in Northwest Louisiana in a generation. The investment includes new utility infrastructure upgrades that will deliver long-term benefits for SWEPC customers and support Amazon's data center operations. All costs associated with these new facilities will be fully covered by Amazon and will not be passed on to existing SWEPACO residential or business customers. The infrastructure investments will strengthen the electric grid, enhance reliability, and help drive long‐term growth and resilience for communities across Northwest Louisiana. This new investment builds on SwePCO's ongoing efforts to modernize and strengthen the grid.\n\n## Story\n\nNe",
