      "published_date": "2024-12-01T00:00:00.000Z",
      "text": "# Combined Cycle Gas Turbine → Area → Resource 1\n\n---\n\n## What is the Sense of Combined Cycle Gas Turbine?\n\nA Combined Cycle Gas Turbine (CCGT) is an electricity generation technology that significantly improves thermal efficiency by utilizing two sequential thermal processes: a gas turbine cycle followed by a steam turbine cycle, recovering waste heat from the gas turbine exhaust to power the second unit. This dual-stage conversion maximizes energy output from a given quantity of natural gas, resulting in a lower heat rate and consequently reduced carbon dioxide emissions per unit of electricity produced compared to simple cycle turbines. CCGT plants represent a transitional technology offering flexible, dispatchable power capacity crucial for stabilizing electrical grids reliant on intermittent renewable sources.\n\n## What is the Past of Combined Cycle Gas Turbine?\n\nThe concept of combining gas and steam cycles dates back to early 20th-century thermodynamic studies, but practical appl",
